{"id": "448bfcc5-8950-4042-af60-13b77d9de29c", "value": "A building for the storage and processing of crops and for housing straw, farm equipment, and occasionally livestock and their fodder. "}
{"id": "23e36d5d-fe52-489a-a22b-f2b7b490753e", "value": "A structure with a roof to provide shelter from the weather for occupants or contents. Use specific type where known."}

{"id": "f971c7ee-0a4f-423a-aa8e-ed6e7d56b7cc", "value": "A soil profile buried beneath later deposits. A relict land surface."}

{"id": "45f6a844-ec6c-48b4-9efe-ea3a7390f89d", "value": "Circular or sub-circular enclosure defined by a bank and (usually internal) ditch, with one or two (rarely more) entrances. Of ceremonial/ritual function, they contain a variety of internal features including timber or stone circles"}

{"id": "7a8988a6-28be-4676-94b5-d2cbe14262e4", "value": "Bas-relief is a type of relief (sculpture) that has less depth to the faces and figures than they actually have, when measured proportionately (to scale). This technique retains the natural contours of the figures, and allows the work to be viewed from many angles without distortion of the figures themselves."}

{"id": "cf7bd6cd-6d50-4d56-b263-b335f8984454", "value": "A decorative design or illustration, often an anthropomorphic or geometrical image, carved into a stone surface, such as a cave wall or free-standing stone. Usually, though not always, of Prehistoric date. "}
{"id": "fb88abf4-a07a-4bdd-ba01-4b4a91f5916a", "value": "A monument featuring a bank or mound constructed primarily of stone."}
{"id": "29ce3c32-9b4c-4944-ad07-92e9fceaaba6", "value": "A lodging for travellers, especially one run by a religious order."}

{"id": "b4889851-ff5c-41a4-99cc-d98011c6cc47", "value": "A long and narrow hollow or trench dug in the ground, often used to carry water, though it may be dry for part of the year. Often for drainage or irrigation of fields. Can also be boundary marker."}
{"id": "62722267-819b-40eb-ab0e-ec541fcf9f06", "value": "The course or channel of a river or stream preserved as a soil feature"}
